@jreback . it appears that pytest is no longer behaving with regex.. could be https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3936. but i've not checked thoroughly.

for the meantime i'm not currently replacing any `with catch_warnings(record=True):
`  or `simplefilter("ignore", DeprecationWarning)` and relying on pytest.

the other alternative is to be less explicit and use `@pytest.mark.filterwarnings("ignore::DeprecationWarning")` and then maybe return at a later date and add `\\nPanel` and `\\n.ix` etc.
